    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nRecently, there were a couple of mappings added to neovim, `v_an`, `v_in`, `]n` and `[n` in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/36993. I think a feature that is missing from this set is the ability to expand the selection to the next and previous sibling nodes using treesitter. I was thinking it might make sense to map those to `]N` and `[N`. Would such an extension be merged if implemented?\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nPressing `]N` in visual mode will expand the selection to the next sibling node, and `[N` will do the same with the previous node.",
